<br>
1. Not get hit (avoidance right?) and to<br>
2. Take less damage when hit (mitigation right?)<br>
<br>
For example lets say an enchanter and a monk had the exact same ALL/ALL low weight items and same HP and were placed in front two adds to the raid. I'm sure we would all agree that the loading please wait would come alot sooner for other classes than us. Now add Stonestane or Voidance discipline plus Mend plus Feign Death. When i am the only person left in the zone after my guild has wiped out, is it any wonder why everyone loves to hate the monk?<br>
<br>
On the raids I go on currently my job is to pull and hopefully live, get up and lay the smack down, watch my aggro, then pull again. When adds comes I may jump out and take it until i see a plate wearer come and take it to try and keep a priest class from biting it, FD then assisting the Main Tank again. <br>
<br>
I have tested the changes on my favorite duo spot and things are just fine. I actually felt the fights may have ended a few seconds earlier and i am sure when i go pull Halls of Testing again I'm gonna die but hey that's what i do..long live da monk <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=195700>Sunol 59 monk</a> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204375>Charlanne 53 Cleric</a>

