Just as warriors with  ac over 1250 got little or no benefit from it.<br>
<br>
This patch has just annoyed me a great deal.<br>
<br>
We lost mitigation, we didn't gain anything, certainly we don't avoid more that was just a rumor.<br>
<br>
I have no faith in Verant to understand the real effects of their choices,  I never main tanked big mobs.<br>
But supposedly because I could tank something like the creator (which slowed a shaman could tank thank you), I'm overpowered.<br>
<br>
The people hardest hit by this are the monks without Good gear.  <br>
<br>
As for taking it personally, I take the nerf personaly yes.<br>
I don't take bonestrikers position personally, nor do I have any ill will toward you.  The only person I find annoying here really is Daesun the ranger who joined this board just to talk about how happy she is this happened.<br>
<br>
The reason I'm outspoken is I don't for a moment imagine the people at verant will do anything to fix this unless people make their feelings well known.  Three years I've played this game, now one morning I wake up to find out that I'm not supposed to be what I am, they nerf my ability to take damage while at the same time improve the defense of plate classes and in pop will give those plate classes with 3 levels of planar toughness (not sure of name) for a 8000hp warrior that means 1200 more hp.<br>
Surely improving them was sufficient.<br>
<br>
I just fail to see why they needed to nerf us while at the same time pump up the other classes.   I'd have no objection to the plate classes getting more hp, but why do I have pay money to buy an expanion in which I become less than I was, while others look forward to being more than they are?<br>
What exactly do monks get in this expansion other than shafted? <br>
